{
  "_doc": {
    "what": "Hand-curated snapshots of Russian missile/strike-weapon stockpiles and monthly production, as estimated by Ukrainian military intelligence (HUR/GUR) and occasionally the Ministry of Defence. These are irregular press disclosures (~twice a year), NOT a scrape — so this file is edited by hand and an ingest script normalises it into the DB.",
    "fields": {
      "as_of": "Date the figures describe (YYYY-MM-DD). See as_of_precision for how exact.",
      "as_of_precision": "day | mid_month | month  — how to read as_of (mid-month dates are our placeholder for 'mid-May' etc.)",
      "reported_at": "Date the estimate was published/disclosed.",
      "source.org": "HUR (Defence Intelligence) | GUR | MoD — the issuing body.",
      "source.via": "Outlet that published it.",
      "stockpile[] / production_monthly[]": "measurements; production is units/month.",
      "type": "single canonical key from missile_types.",
      "types": "array of canonical keys when ONE number lumps several systems (combined=true).",
      "combined": "true when a single reported number covers >1 canonical type (the 'not specified' case).",
      "raw_label": "verbatim wording from the source, kept for audit.",
      "value": "the number; for bound=range it is the LOW end and value_max the high end.",
      "bound": "up_to (≤) | at_least (≥, 'more than'/'over'/'200+') | approx ('about'/'nearly'/'~') | exact | range | planned"
    },
    "known_issues": [
      "Taxonomy drift: early reports lump Iskander (no M/K split) and Kh-101/Kh-55/Kh-35; later ones split them. Modelled via combined=true.",
      "Two reports weeks apart can disagree (mid-May vs mid-June 2025). Both are kept verbatim.",
      "The ~11,000 'S-300P/S-400 air-defence missiles' figure (Jun 2025) is the whole SAM pool, a different thing from the RM-48U strike count (~400-450). Keyed s300_s400_ad and flagged.",
      "Nov 2022 (MoD) is a consumption ledger (pre-war / used / made / remaining); only the 'remaining' values are recorded here, so it is sparse.",
      "Aug 2023 production figures were stated as monthly *plans*, not confirmed output (bound=planned).",
      "Absent != zero: a type missing from a report was not disclosed that period, not counted as 0. Time-series charts must render a GAP, not a drop to zero. Some reports are partial (e.g. 2025-07-10 is ballistic-only).",
      "The bound qualifier must drive rendering: floor-framed ('600','over 300') vs ceiling-framed ('up to 500') reports otherwise manufacture fake volatility. See the 2025-05 vs 2025-06 notes."
    ]
  },

